{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, silicone bread mat, kitchen towel, pizza tray, baking paper, rolling pin, round cookie cutter (5 cm), plastic wrap, pastry brush, oven","id":"r107104","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-duv9SQZpxWo\/XZavCzs-KLI\/AAAAAAAAhqo\/rOenJvT71cM-N_9fq4KU3IpDo8cpJQuZwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_XoM67uRREax_Tnu6.png","title":"Hazelnut chocolate brioche","publishedAt":"2017-03-19T00:00:00Z","ingredients2":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Brioche"},{"content":"oil, for greasing"},{"content":"180 g full cream milk"},{"content":"60 g white sugar"},{"content":"1 tsp dried yeast"},{"content":"60 g unsalted butter, melted"},{"content":"450 g baker's flour"},{"content":"1 tsp salt"},{"content":"2 eggs, lightly beaten"},{"content":"300 g hazelnut chocolate spread (see Tips)"},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Glaze"},{"content":"1 egg yolk"},{"content":"15 g full cream milk"},{"content":"icing sugar, to serve (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"6.1 g","fat":"11.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"36.9 g","calories":"1161 kJ \/ 276 kcal"},"preparations2":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Brioche"},{"content":"Lightly grease a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place milk into mixing bowl and warm <b>1 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add sugar, yeast and butter and warm <b>2 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add flour, salt and eggs and mix <b>6 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then knead <b>4 min\/<b>."},{"content":"Transfer dough onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface and knead dough by hand until it isn't sticky. Shape into a ball and place into thermal serving bowl or other large bowl. Cover with a kitchen towel and leave to prove in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 1 hour). Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Line a pizza tray (30 cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Knock down dough, then transfer onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface. Knead dough a few times and shape into a log (approx. 25 cm). Flatten dough ball slightly and cut into 4 equal portions. Roll each portion into a ball."},{"content":"Flatten each ball with your hand, then roll out dough portions into a circle (approx. 30 cm diameter, 3-4 mm thickness)."},{"content":"Place 1 dough circle onto prepared pizza tray and spread with ⅓ of the hazelnut chocolate spread, leaving a 1 cm edge. Place another dough circle on top of spread and cover with ⅓ of the hazelnut chocolate spread, leaving a 1 cm edge. Repeat with a third dough circle and remaining ⅓ hazelnut chocolate spread. Top with remaining dough circle and trim excess dough from edges."},{"content":"Using a cooking cutter (5 cm) or the rim of a drinking glass, press lightly into centre of dough to make a light imprint."},{"content":"Cut dough into quarters (do not cut through inner circle imprint). Cut each quarter in halves (do not cut through inner circle), creating 8 sections. Then cut each eighth into halves (do not cut through inner circle) - you will have a total of 16 sections."},{"content":"Holding 2 neighbouring segments by the ends, twist outwards twice.. Pull ends together and pinch to seal. Repeat with remaining sections to create a total of 8 twisted portions. The brioche will look like a flower. Cover with plastic wrap. Leave to prove in a warm place for 20 minutes."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Glaze"},{"content":"Place egg yolk and milk into mixing bowl and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"Lightly brush brioche with glaze. Bake for 20-25 minutes (180°C), until golden brown."},{"content":"Allow to cool and dust with icing sugar (optional) before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To make your own hazelnut chocolate spread, please refer to the recipe in <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em>.","This recipe was contributed by Marshia Radin."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","2h","16 portions"]}